# Cursor Rules

IMPORTANT:
- files should not exceed 200 lines
- documentation should be very brief and concise (1 line per feature when possible)
- ALWAYS follow feature development workflow (see `.cursor/rules/features.mdc`)

## Page Layout
- The page is split into parts vertically using a decimal system
- 0.0 to 1.0 represents the first page
- 1.0 to 2.0 represents the second page
- 2.5 represents the middle of page 3
- Generally: floor(value) + 1 = page number, decimal = position within page
- URL scrolling: `#pos=X` or `?pos=X` auto-scrolls to position (300ms, pos=0 = no scroll)

## Development Server
- Project runs on `http://localhost:8080` (npm run start)
- NEVER start/stop the dev server - user handles this
- Dev server is always assumed to be running

## Testing Visible Features
- ALWAYS test visible features using MCP Playwright after implementation
- Navigate to `http://localhost:8080` or `http://localhost:8080/?pos=X` to test specific scroll positions
- Take screenshots to verify changes are working correctly
- Close Playwright browser after testing
- Furthermore you can add console logs and read the logs from the browser